Fixes #1614.

This was a consequence of my attempt to fix another bug where proof tree filters (e.g., "hide closed subtrees") wouldn't be applied correctly when switching between multiple proofs. This fix was to redraw the proof tree, which lead to the selected node becoming unselected. Now, the proof tree is redrawn if necessary, and then the view scrolls to the previously selected node as it should.

