Apparently, there were some old proof files which failed to load after !399 (noticed by Wolfram @pfeifer).

**Reproduce/Test behavior:** [unloadable.zproof](/uploads/d0fe0d71aee38d6c366cf07a58fdd209/unloadable.zproof) fails to load after !399 and loads again after this fix

**Cause:**
!399 translates `Throwable(String, Throwable)` in javaRedux into
```
   public Throwable(java.lang.String arg0, java.lang.Throwable arg1) {
       //@ set message = arg0;
       //@ set cause = arg1;
       ;
   }
```
Old/after fix:
```
   public Throwable(java.lang.String arg0, java.lang.Throwable arg1) {
       //@ set message = arg0;
       ;
       //@ set cause = arg1;
       ;
   }
```

**Notes:**
The previous KeY behavior was to create empty statements in `JMLTransformer.java` for `@set` annotations at the bottom of a method. But one for each comment, not one for all comments. Now, the same behavior is copied to `ProofJavaProgramFactory.java`. Sorry, I should have noticed this earlier.

In principle, it would be nice to remove all artificial `EmptyStatement`s. But to be compatible this fix even adds more empty statements.

This MR provides a fix for #1582. Also two additional test cases are added. There could be more testcases.

This does currently not solve all problematic cases. For example, the assignable clauses of these two contracts
```
/*@ requires r1;
  @ ensures e1;
  @ assignable \strictly_nothing;
  @
  @ also
  @
  @ requires !r1;
  @ ensures e2;
  @ assignable \nothing;
  @*/
```
are combined into
```
  \if (r1) \then (∅) \else (allLocs)
∩ \if (¬r1) \then (∅«impl») \else (allLocs)
```
I am not sure what the exact purpose of this term label is and whether we should ignore it for combination or not.
